President Cyril Ramaphosa will meet with the business constituency, presented at the National Economic Development and Labour Council (Nedlac) on Friday afternoon. The bilateral meeting will discuss the economic reconstruction and recovery plan aimed to create jobs, re-industrialise the economy and accelerate economic reforms. The business sector says this is a rare opportunity they’ve been waiting for. “Black Business Council and BUSA will engage in a bilateral meeting with President Cyril Ramaphosa. The meeting the first of its kind before SONA will solicit business views before the State of the Nation address,” says Black Business Council’s  Kganki Matabane. Video | President Ramaphosa addresses NEDLAC on economic recovery [February 2021] 